draw((1,0)--(1,5),linewidth(1));
draw((2,0)--(2,5),linewidth(1));
draw((3,0)--(3,5),linewidth(1));
draw((4,0)--(4,5),linewidth(1));
draw((5,0)--(5,5),linewidth(1));

[/asy]

Solution:
We do some simplification, taking advantage of the fact that $n! = n\cdot (n-1)!$: \begin{align*}
\frac{9!\cdot 5!\cdot 2!}{8!\cdot 6!} &= \frac{9\cdot 8! \cdot 5! \cdot 2}{8!\cdot 6\cdot 5!}\\
&= \frac{9\cdot 2}{6}\\
&= \boxed{3}.
\end{align*}

