\end{cases}
\]If the graph $y=f(x)$ is continuous, find the sum of all possible values of $n$.

Part of the graph of $f(x) = ax^3 + bx^2 + cx + d$ is shown. What is $b$?

[asy]
unitsize(1.5 cm);

