\[\sqrt{(x + t)^2 + (y + t)^2} = \sqrt{(x - t)^2 + (y - t)^2} + d.\]Squaring both sides, we get
\[(x + t)^2 + (y + t)^2 = (x - t)^2 + (y - t)^2 + 2d \sqrt{(x - t)^2 + (y - t)^2} + d^2.\]This simplifies to
\[4tx + 4ty - d^2 = 2d \sqrt{(x - t)^2 + (y - t)^2}.\]Squaring both sides, we get
